CatDescriptText: Mr. Walter Loomis, 8422 Bricelyn Street, was part of the Pittsburghers Speak Up column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 26, 1957, pg. 4, with question: "Do you believe we should have a state law forbidding strikes of trolley cars, buses, and taxicabs?" answer reads: "I think there should be a law forbidding all strikes if the workers are gettting a decent salary."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Walter Loomis wearing moustache and light colored apron, standing in front of a bar with bottles, mirrors, cash register, and box of "El Producto" cigars
